  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QC Inspector",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:   </strong></p><ul><li>Perform set-up/in-process/ outgoing inspection for production\nparts as per quality plans when necessary. Responsible for maintaining detailed\nrecords of inspections, test results, and any deviations from the quality standards.   </li></ul><ul><li> Stop production if quality problems are detected during set up or in-process\nproduction, report to production m/c setter / toolmaker to rectify quality\nproblems. Raise PRF and ensure rejected parts are properly identified at designated\narea.   </li><li>Perform outgoing inspection before packing.</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure there is Inspection status identification on production\nparts upon inspection.</li></ul><ul><li>Isolation / purging of rejected parts from good parts to avoid\nparts mix-up.</li></ul><ul><li>Perform last piece inspection after production (or) tool down and\nreport to toolmaker for corrections/improvements</li><li>Update Control Charts (X-bar/R-Charts) and CPK Data as per quality\nplans.</li></ul><ul><li>Other duties assigned by the superior and management.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Secondary Education or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 2 years inspection experience, preferably in stamping industry.</li><li>Operate measuring equipment such as Smartscope, Profile projector, Toolmakers’scope, Height Gauge, etc.\nSimple communication in English. Basic SPC knowledge for X-bar charts & CPK.</li><li>Interpretation of technical drawings, basic geometric dimensioning & tolerancing, common metal stamping\nquality problems, interpret and apply sampling plans for visual inspection.\nBasic computer understanding to input datas.</li></ul>",
